caption: Great food, drinks, service, and atmosphere! No wait at 9am on a weekday
Only 4 miles off tge I-10. A fabulous pit stop, fantastic breakfast for a good price. We will atop again on our travel thrus.
Chicken and waffles was delicious👌🏾

This was so absolutely delicious and such a great environment on a Friday morning. I had the breakfast sandwich with bacon and my husband had the Cajun Benedict. We did a side of a chocolate chip pancake and a side of gumbo. The power was out when we arrived but it honestly just added to the quaint and calm environment. The service was very nice, despite having read warnings of horrendous wait times. We were seated immediately and didn't have to wait long for anything we needed. The praline bacon was what dreams are made of, but we were a little surprised to see it only came with 2 full pieces for the entire appetizer. Definitely recommend!!

The staff were very friendly, the mimosas were great, and the food was excellent. I had the Cajun Benedict and my wife had a breakfast sandwich. I highly recommend either. My Cajun Benedict came with gumbo in place of the hollandaise sauce, and their gumbo is so good! My wife even got a side of gumbo for herself.

AMAZING just to start out... The food was FANTASTIC!!! Our waiter was on it, never ran out of drinks (coffee was hot, strong and fresh) and he checked on us at the perfect times. The food was so fresh and hot that I had to wait to for it cool before I could eat, plus it was freaking DELICIOUS!!! We WILL be going back.

I had the Croque Madame with fries and it was delicious.  I was with a group of 5 friends and everyone enjoyed their entrees and drinks. The service was great and the place has an upbeat atmosphere.  They do serve mimosas but if you're looking for a bottomless special, this is not the place. Overall, great experience and a great place to enjoy brunch.
Great food, atmosphere, and staff. Fun location in downtown Lafayette.
Amazing food with terrific service! Best brunch in town!

Amazing food.  Pancakes, breakfast sandwich, and potatoes were all delicious. The catfish bites came with a dipping condiment that was particularly enjoyable.  It was a horseradish mustard.  Normally I do not care for either flavor, but this was delicately balanced, not at all over flavored.  It was wonderful and surprising.  Most enjoyable of all was the Cajun Benedict.  I hesitated ordering it, worrying the bread would be mushy in texture.  The cheese kept the structure of the bread.  The dark roux gumbo was perfect.  My only regret is that I live four hours away.

One of the best places to meet up with friends and family for some absolutely wonderful food. Atmosphere is so relaxing and you are always treated like family plus prices won't be outrageous yet very affordable and worth every penny.
Outstanding food, local, great service

My family wait 1 hour to eat brunch. We are a party of 6. While waiting for our table there was 2 other group that came after us that was served before us. Both parties was consist of 4 and 6 people. Why did they get served before us??

Arrived around 1pm for brunch (they close at 2p) and I was worried that after a long morning the staff might be rushed a little bit towards closing. That wasn't the case at all. Our server was very patient and kind. Great customer service. Our food didn't take long at all. And it was excellent. My date had the breakfast sandwich and she loved it. I had the french toast and it was one of the best french toast I've had. My only complaint might be the portions...they were pretty large. Neither of us had an appetite at dinner and ended up just having snacks the rest of the day. Absolutely enjoyed my experience at The French Press.
The food was great and so was the service definitely worth the trip. Our waitress Chloe was extremely nice and all around wonderful. Definitely would go back
Delicious coffee and PoBoys
I've had the boudin ball poboy (with bacon potato salad) and breakfast sandwich (with chipotle cheddar grits) here and they were excellent.
Nice brunch spot. I love the blackened red fish poboy with fries.
Croque madame was amazing! I love traditional eggs Benedict and this twist was fantastic. Breakfast gumbo is best way to describe it. Btw, the gumbo is legit.
OMG this Cajun Eggs Benedict is to die for!

The French Press is one of those perfect little places that just blow your mind with their food, drinks and service.  The food, is so indescribably good and I love their unique take on traditional cafe fare.  Their cheddar waffles and steens cane chicken is so good, like sinfully good.  Pair it with their praline bacon and you’re in for a delightful treat.  Our waiter, LJ was attentive, knowledgeable and super friendly he is a great server. We also asked some specific questions about the ingredients in some menu items as our daughter has a large amount of food allergies.  He was able to tell us specifics and give us enough detail that we would feel incredibly comfortable bringing her here as well.  Thank you so much for such a wonderful dining experience!
Very rustic and vintage feel.  Good drinks and food. My guests didn't like the pepper jelly on the chicken and waffles.  But I enjoyed the cajun Benedict.

Not only was the food amazing but so our waitress Rikki. She made our experience even more delightful. What a pleasant personality she possesses.  A good waitress is a testament to a businesses attention to detail. We will be returning sooner than later. 💕
We stopped here for breakfast during the Festival International in 2018. Definitely worth getting up early to be first in line.
I simply enjoyed their dishes. I always get awesome customer service there. The place is well kept and the employees are always very nice. Would recommend to others.

We we so eager to come and visit this place. We heard so many good things about it. We arrived on a Saturday morning. I ordered a mimosa which was ok. Th menu made it seem more extravagant. Anywho. I went on to order the shrimp wrap. When the server delivered the food I immediately smelled a strong fishy/seafood smell. I just thought it was fresh to order. Unfortunately, as soospoil took a bite I tasted a strong unfamiliar taste. I went on to take a another bite and the taste of something Spoiled/Sour lite my taste bands. I didn't eat anymore and told the server the shrimp was not fresh. It was spoiled She was nice and offered another item. This happened on yesterday. I have not stopped using the bathroom since. My stomach is a wreck and I am hoping it doesn't get worst :-(.
This was one of the best burgers I've ever had!! The vibe was on point and servers were super friendly!

Been here a few times food is pretty good and the ambiance if the building is amazing, used to be on old printting press building. I suggest if you plan on coming here at peek weekend brunch hours you make a resso. The food is like modern american breakfast with a cajun twist its very much a Sunday morning kinda spot.
Excellent spot to have something when in a rush. Their customer service is prompt, prices are fair, fantastic vibes. Will come visit again
There Cajun Egg Benedict with fried shrimp or oyster. U got to try it. AH..!

I hosted my wedding reception here. Small intimate and absolutely perfect. Service was amazing. The owners are delightful to work with and SO accommodating. I recommend this spot to anyone! Brunch or private event they will not let you down!

First of all, I’ve been here many times because the food is amazing every time and I worked near this place for a while.  Highlight on menu: Sweet Baby Breezus  This is like Nirvana (blissful heaven, not the grunge band) exploded into your mouth with the power of a Chuck Norris roundhouse, rendering you unable to speak or even just identify yourself.  Only issue: Inconsistent quality of service.  The service here is all over the place. You might have an amazing experience or you might have a nightmare service experience.  Ps. The “nightmare” experience has never been due to rudeness. It has always been due to understaffing.  Obviously, the food is good enough to keep me going back, so it can’t be terrible.
Wait is sometimes to long, food can be hit or miss. Needs bigger kitchen

We cut a trip short in NOLA, pulled up this place for breakfast. Best decision the whole trip. I had the chicken and waffles, amazing..no syrup needed because the chicken has a glaze that sits on a buttermilk cheese waffle...my son had the cajun Benedict...wow, he doesn't get adventurous often but it blew him away!

Recently visited Lafayette and stopped at a ton of restaurants but this was our favorite! The menu was incredible, the prices were so reasonable, the staff was incredibly friendly, and it was a great atmosphere. My husband and I split a variety of items and everything was insanely good.
Great breakfast food with some good Cajun twists!
Food was delicious. Service was good. If anything the prices were a little high. But it's all great quality and original recipes. So it's understandable
Great food but not worth the regularly 30-45mins wait for a table and slow service.

I wish I could give this more starts. I truly do, because the food was great, and the coffee was good (for American coffee that is.)  The true issue here is the speed of service. Though friendly and helpful, it did take a while before getting service. Bordering on me walking out of the establishment all together.  We spent 1,5 hours in this place, taking an hour between being seated, and getting our food.  So don't go here if you're in a hurry. But if you have the time do check it out.  --- Edit  Went again today, knowing full well that it was going to be a long wait. The food really is amazing. And dare I say, worth the wait.  Try this place if you have the time.
Gourmet, Delicious, Delectable are just a few words that come to mind. Not too expensive and well worth the wait.

So after sitting here for 30 minutes the waitress finally comes over and says your food will be right out. Then one of group is told “they’re working on yours” then they come back and say we don’t have the shrimp for your order. Really! That member didn’t have lunch. Which is my new boss and I picked the restaurant! Very disappointed after such good reviews. The food we did get was good but we had plastic In one of the sandwiches. I felt the manager should have come out and apologized at the very least.
The wait was centuries long. We literally waited over an hour for 4 dishes at 12pm and they were incredibly salty.
Best restaurant in Lafayette
Food is Amazing!!

This guy next to me have been waiting for an hour.   The waitress put there fingers on the tip of the straws and then finger in the glasses. I saw dirty glasses being filled with water.  Then she rubbed the dirty glasses from the inside to get stuff out...hardly anyone has food on table..they need more cooks ..less waiting staff.  This one waitress thought another waitress took one of her glasses and was about to RIP it from her before another waitress said she has done it..  this place has gotten worse .. dont come here if your hungry..
One of our favorite restaurants. Always good food and good service.
Slowest kitchen in town is iMonelli's. Second slowest is The French Press.

This place has a lot of potential. 3 years ago, it was really good,  but has declined significantly over the past year. The service is extremely slow. Waited over an hour and a half for food and the resturant wasn't even packed. The eggs on the breakfast sandwich was so soggy and runny, it was not edible. Something needs to change.
A cool, close-knit brunch spot. I prefer coffee in a french press so this is a no-brainer for me. Get the Sweet Baby Breesus. I could go for that every day.

So we tried this spot for a Sunday brunch..BEFORE the rush. Got there around 9:30 and there wasn't a big wait. They have a variety of mimosas if y'all are into that. A buddy of ours got the French press coffee and it was neat having a French press at French press haha. Okay to the food- truffle fries were A1. Frog legs taste like mini chicken. And the Cajun Benedict. Straight . Super powerful taste. But overall amazing. My homegirl got the chicken and waffles and that also looked really good. Try it out y'all.

The food here is pretty good, but the service isn't great. The food takes quite a while to come out. Also when we ordered a salad with dressing on the side, it was instead served with the dressing in the salad.
Food is great but expect to wait a long time for food.
Slow

Beautiful building. Extremely slow, neglectful service. The waiters tended to prioritize people ordering drinks before those who aren't, which makes sense as for the most part; however, it took us thirty minutes to order and the only reason it didn't take longer was I asked a waitress as we were walking by if she could find our waitress for us. She asked us for our waitress's name or what she looked like. I couldn't even say because we had been handed around so many times to so many different waitresses. The food then took another forty minutes to come out. During this time, my waitress asked me if I wanted more coffee, then she forgot to bring it to me. Part of this is not her fault. With the amount of drinks being served here, the restaurant desperately needs to hire more waitstaff. In addition, I ordered eggs benedict and couldn't even eat more than three bites due to the roux being so disgustingly dark. There wasn't even bread on the side or any rice to break through the immense oil from the roux. Overall, this was a terrible experience.

Honestly wait time was awful. I don’t think I’ve ever had to wait over an hour for cold potatoes and sub par breakfast sandwiches. We didn’t have a large party either, just the two of us eating at the bar. When we asked about the food at the 45 minute mark, the waitress informed us it usually takes 30-45 minutes to get food out. I’m not going to touch much on how crazy that is, they must have one cook in the kitchen. I will say however, we proceeded to wait another 15 minutes on top of asking her to check on our food before we got it. I’ve never felt the need to leave a negative review before, but this place was honestly garbage in terms of literally everything. Just wild, place needs to change something.
(Translated by Google) Nice place for breakfast  (Original) Endroit sympa pour le petit-déjeuner

Just go! The food is so good! We had brunch at The French Press in downtown Lafayette and it did not disappoint! First we had a pot of their fantastic french press coffee, then we ordered food. I had Grits And Grillades my husband had Sweet Baby Breesus my Son and DIL had Chicken And Waffles and Croque Monsieur. I had a bite of all the dishes and wow I will be back the next chance I can.
Fantastic service.  The Cajun Poutine was amazing.  Their version of the eggs Benedict are a must have!

I can’t recommend anything on the menu because it is all so delicious! I’ve never had a bad meal or bad service. The price is decent and the atmosphere sets the mood for a great brunch with friends. If you visit this fine establishment, you MUST get a mimosa.

I LOVE The French Press, it is always a treat to be able to go. The only reason I do not give it 5 stars is because they no longer do Eggs Benedict which was never on the menu, but they would do it if you asked. My tastebuds melted the first time I went and they did not have it anymore. Still delicious and I love me some Baby Breesus!
The food was good but we waited nearly 1 hr for 2 breakfast sandwiches. I asked 40 minutes into the wait how much longer and they told me it would be right out then 20 more minutes went by.
Servers were friendly. Press coffee was so good it almost touches your soul.
Attended Poppy Tookers Drag Queen Brunch! What a fun, fun time! Food was very good and lots of it!! Fantastic deal! Hope they continue this in the future.

Even though the food is quite delicious and it has a nice atmosphere, the wait was absolutely too long. After ordering our food it took over 45 minutes for it to come out. This was my second time going there to give it another chance. This place apparently is known for food taking to long to come out. They need to work on timeliness.
Great food.  Boudin ball poboy and pork chop poboy are a must.
The truffle fries are amazing
We waited for over 45 minutes for a seat and then another 30+ for our food that was mediocre.  Decent beer selection tho!
Great food, but a bit of a delay in service.

I have to give 2 stars because our experience (a table of 5) was less than pleasant. We ordered 10 minutes after sitting and waited an hour and 20 minutes for our food. We were barely spoken to during that time and had to ask for a manager to see what was going on, while other tables were getting in and leaving before we ever even got our food. Our waitress was very sweet but it just seemed like there was something going wrong on the kitchen. Once we got our food, things were missing from our plates, and we had to ask twice for silverware. And then only some of us got some forks, no knives or spoons. So we had to also ask for those. The manager apologized and gave us 30% off. I will have to update this when I go again but our service wasn’t great.
Always good food
This is a pretty cool joint. The antique feel coupled with the environment is a sweet combination. The food is like nothing you've ever had before! And the pancakes... OH MY GOODNESS! A must have!!!!
Succulent french food, nice decor & high ceiling, nice waitress. Get your fix here when you're in Lafayette
Yum! 100% will be back
My family and I visited the restaurant one Sunday during brunch. The food was great and the staff were very friendly.
Food was amazing
Great brunch!
Takes too long to get my order
The best Breakfast brunch I have ever had!  # awsome
Despite the long wait time, the food was great and our server was awesome,we had alot of people, she was very kind and polite. Can't recall what her name was but her name starts with M, maybe malorie
Unbelievable food! Such flavors!

So we tried this spot for a Sunday brunch..BEFORE the rush. Got there around 9:30 and there wasn't a big wait. They have a variety of mimosas if y'all are into that. A buddy of ours got the French press coffee and it was neat having a French press at French press haha. Okay to the food- truffle fries were A1. Frog legs taste like mini chicken.
Sweetest staff ever ❤️
THIS IS A MUST FOR EVERYONE...CAJUN EGG BENEDICT 🤗🤗
Wait time for food way too long!
Nice atmosphere. Great service. Fantastic food. I will be going back for brunch again and will also try out the lunch menu.
Excellent coffee. I had the blueberry pancakes. They were delicious and I couldn't finish them all! Service was great and atmosphere is charming.
Different but tasty food. Nice place for a family feast. I suggest trying either the Cajun Benedict or the Shrimp/Grits.
Went to the Father's Day buffet and there wasn't anything I tasted that I wouldn't recommend. Every morsel was delicious!
Waiting for an hour so far. No food yet
Food is awesome and mimosa had the grits and grillades and bacon. Egg avocado on toasted croissant amazing staff interesting
Great food, but a loooooong wait for it.
Great breakfast/brunch spot. Food was amazing. Don't go if your in a hurry, but worth the wait!
Very nice place was hung over as Hell....Lol.

5 star food. 1 star service. Incredibly slow and inefficient seating process. Nice waitstaff with zero sense of urgency. Food takes 40 minutes or more to come out. I really wish the service was better.

I really like the food here and have tried to give this place a chance so many times. But it never fails, every time I go it takes hours for someone to take my order and for the food to arrive. For example, today I got there for noon. It took 20 minutes for someone to take our order. We finally received our order after 1:00 pm. It tooks over 40 minutes. The last time I went for lunch, they took so long that my friend had to leave before he even received his food. Obviously, this is a problem that will never be resolved. Today will be the last day I ever eat at French Press.
Worth the wait!  Great food and drinks too 😉

Delicious and wonderful atmosphere! Food takes a minute to come out, but it is so worth it! I split the French toast with a friend and got the candied bacon appetizer. Wonderful! I had a bit of everything that came to our table of friends and loved everything!
Amazing food. The Sweet Baby Breezus and Cajun Benedict are now my favorite foods! Can't wait to come back!

Tons of potential for this restaurant located in Downtown Lafayette. Server (Camille) was very nice and friendly and probably the best part of our visit. However upon arrival we had a 10 minute wait to be seated when there were at least three tables available that needed to be cleaned. There was really no sense of urgency to get us seated and made the situation feel somewhat awkward. Out appetizer of Truffle Fries came out relatively quickly and were very good. Once we ordered our food the service was very slow. I did not time how long it took our food to come out but it was much longer than usual. Not only did the food take an extensive amount of time but it did not all come out at the same time. Food was very good and had a great presentation. Overall this restaurant has unlimited potential because of the setting they have created and the unique food that they serve but they must do better in regards to the timing of their service.
Had an amazing chicken sliders with grits and fell in love. Awesome atmosphere, fun staff, and decent portion sizes.
Cajun Benny is always good for your soul

Sad day at the French Press. No boudan, no Chicken and never got my breakfast. Very frustrating for a place that's supposed to be good. Waiter never bothered to let us know breakfast wasn't coming. After 30 min we ask ? He says something to the affect only one cook, it's coming. He did manage 5 or 10 min later to deliver the granola and yogurt. "Your sandwich is coming"  anyway we had a meeting to go too, cancelled the sandwich and got the bill. Which is I didn't Chase them and go to the register would have taken longer than the sandwich. Seems the place has collapsed. Of our radar now. The bacon was good.

Food was good. Very unorganized and does not seem to have it together. From time of arrival 30 minute wait. When seared ordered our food took almost an hour to get it. My dish was delivered to the wring table. By the server of this table. Dropped off wrong food and did not catch the mistake. The gentleman who was given my food order Gumbo and was given my breakfast sandwich and instead of saying this is not what was order he took a bite. So now they have to rwmake my food. Another 10 to 15 minutes. I got a apology but that was about it. As said need to be more organized

I have been to restaurant on a prior occasion when passing through LAFAYETTE and it was very tasty and memorable. My last visit was aweful. We were told that the prior cook had “walked out the weekend prior.” I wish management would have seen the value in this cook that decided to vacate the premises. Our food was aweful!! We ordered the blackened shrimp poboy. The shrimp were BURNT!! The cook returned our plates to us via the waitress saying that “it’s supposed to be that way.” My friend decided to order the gumbo to replace her meal and she stated that tasted like roux! It was very dark. To add the insult....the cook did not want to credit our bill!! The waitress had told us it was up to the cook. We did still ask for management which made every right!  Service provided by the waitress was great!! I forget her name however her husband was from France! 😊  I only would recommend if the cook has been replaced. The one they have now is VERY arrogant!

Food was very good. Service was extremely slow and seemed to be confused. After waiting over 30 minutes for our food one of our party got there food and the rest of our food was given to other people. They were apologetic and remade our food fairly quick.
Great

My eyes had seen glory!  I tried to refocus my eyes back to the menu so I could find something.  The waitress walked up and asked what we wanted to eat.  My friend asked if I wanted a mimosa and I was like SURE! Didn't realize there was different kinds, this girl was hooked! So, I went ahead and ordered the breakfast sandwich with goat cheese and my friend ordered the chicken and waffles.  That darn sandwich with that goat cheese was EVERYTHING!!! I started taking small bites to savor every bit of that sandwich.  His chicken and waffles was out of this world.
SWEET BABY BREESUS Food was amazing!
Such press!  Very wow!

Service was the right amount. Our server kept his distance, but checked in on us at the appropriate times. Food takes a while to come out, but is completely worth the wait. The Cajun Benedict was excellent.
I never had a biscuit stuffed with bacon and boudin topped with steen syrup!!!! My side of cheddar grits were on point! I ate every last bit of it!

Went in here for Breakfast on our way out of town. We were seated quickly and proceeded to wait forever for our waiter. They were busy, but they werent packed. We ordered our food and waited... and waited... and waited some more. We finally asked how long our food would be after about 30 mins and were were told at least 30 mins more. We advised our waiter we would be leaving to which he replied that he would check on our food. Came back and they hadnt even started our ticket yet. We left. 2 stars as the place looked nice?

I ordered fried catfich bites. They tell me 30 minutes later that they are out of fish so it’ll be replaced with shrimp. Ok, I’m starting to get aggrivated now. An hour and a half later, and I still have yet to receive my order. It wasn’t until two hours after I arrived that I finally received it, even noticing that some people who arrived before me received their order before I did. Ridiculous.  I recommend eating here if you find enjoyment in waiting and receiving food that you didn’t order.
Really amazing food, but every time I come here we are always waiting at least 20 minutes for our food.
The service was bad. The waitress was unfriendly.  The food was ok but took forever to come out.
Best brunch in town
Great food but takes awhile to get it. Rather noisy but quaint atmosphere.
Delicious food,  fast & friendly service.
Service is pretty good, food is always great.

Food was absolutely delish...saw this place recommended in roadtrippers on our travels from Orlando FL To California and we are very happy we chose to stop here. James was very courteous and efficient. Not too far off of I10....make the trip...its worth it. French toast was devine
Great brunch spot- excellent good and cocktails
The food is superb; my recommendation is anything on the menu. (Gumbo breakfast is amazing) The service was outstanding: attentive but never obtrusive. The atmosphere is ideal. Great breakfast place!
Great food but hope you have time to wait. Takes along time to get your food.
Breakfast was very good. Place clean, bloody mary's were the best.

The server was very nice and friendly. The food took about an hour to arrive. It was mediocre. We ordered the cajun Benedict and the acadian egg and cheese. I had 2 bites of the Benedict until I found 2 good size egg shells in it. Second time coming here and I don't think I'll be back. If you're really hungry and don't want to wait an hour or more for your food, I don't recommend coming here.
Excellent food and beautiful ambience
Coffee wasnt Starbucks

We arrived right as they opened on Saturday morning, and were delighted with the menu. With 3 hungry adults and 3 hungry kids, and hour of waiting was just too much. I would go back for sure, just better educated about how long it may take. Our server, Courtney, was great, although very busy. The stuffed French toast was the best, and the Sweet Baby Breesus also very good my daughter wasn’t happy i forgot to order her gravy On the side of the chicken fried steak, but i didn’t mind since that meant she didn’t want it and the adults got to eat it. . It was very good.
Food is AMAZING and the service was perfect. Rikki is a phenomenal server, ask for her and you will get the best service around.

Grits and grillades were cooked perfectly. Mom got the Cajun Benedict and it was as filling as the menu suggested. Both dishes came out hot and quick. I added Tabasco sauce but I'm always adding some zing to my dishes.  The picture is of two medium poached eggs over chicken and sausage gumbo. Delicious.
Great food
Great service great food and a pretty waitress
Delicious!
Good food for good $
Hosted oure rehearsal dinner, very good service and food.
Very good
Very unique.  You have to have Canun Benedict once in your life.
Fantastic gem in Lafayette with nice little twists on classic Cajun, French, and Creole cuisine. Huge portions, fantastic service, left with a full stomach and a smile on my face!
Awesome as always. Best pressed coffee in town!

Today the service is not good. We were seated at a dirty table with food all over the chairs. Waitress asking us for IDs and no one asked the really young people next to us. Disappointing, because I really like coming here
Restaurant was unclean. Food was great though.
I highly recommend this place
Food was delicious but it took forever to come to us and it didnt seem busy so that was odd. Cute atmosphere too

I would love to give this place a better review this is the place my boyfriend would mom stop talk about because of how great the food is. But our server was awful. She spend 20 mintues talking to a coupke near the fron of the building. Causing her to not take our drink order and then forget our orders. I had to as the girl behind the "bar" to help us.  But I will say order sweet baby bresus and the praline bacon. Soooo good.
The best chicken and waffles I'v ever had my life
Best breakfast.  Must try the soups!
(Translated by Google) The food is fine, although the service is a bit slow. They could improve on that.  (Original) La comida está bien, aunque el servicio es un poco lento. Podrían mejorar en eso.

Service was excellent, food was pretty good but a bit higher priced, and the wait was loooooooooooong. Way too long for the portion sizes we got. We were seated quickly and got drinks quickly, but the food took over an hour to arrive. It was a bit busy, so it was somewhat understandable, but expect it if you go in a weekend.

I'm sure it tastes fabulous if you can stomach the wait.... I waited over 30 minutes until a guy came in an asked about his to go order.... he waited 20 more minutes next to me until I asked when my order might arrive... told she didn't want to guess "in case its longer, I dont want you to be disappointed"... but maybe 30 minutes?? Too late, already sad. So I bounced out. Hope the to go guy managed to get a refund or his order :/
Wonderful place for a friendly gathering. Reminds me of being in New Orleans. The food was beautifully prepared and delicious.
Relaxed atmosphere. But great service and food! Very welcoming place.

First time here two days ago and while we were taken aback by both the prices and the wait time for our food, it was all 100% worth it. Zero regrets and we went home with leftovers. We arrived around 10:45 and ate around noon. The chicken and waffles was to die for. My husband couldn't stop eating from my plate and I can guarantee it's what we are ordering next time as well! Ace!

We stopped by this place before we continue on for our road trip. There's limited street parking so we parked at the garage near by, which is not too far of a walk. The server took a while to get to us for seating. We ordered the Cajun breakfast and chicken & waffles. The cajun breakfast dish was extremely salty which I had three glasses of water for it. The chicken and waffle was covered in syrup, which literally taste so sweet that it was unbearable. I would never come back again for the food. Everything tastes way too much out of proportion in terms of taste.

Great food! Busy atmosphere. We got here around 10:15 and were going to wait for a table but sat at the bar. Really busy! Great food! I got the breakfast sandwich with goat cheese and a side of cheese grits. My husband got the stuffed French toast. So good and they have great coffee too!

The place has a relaxed atmosphere and the interior is tastefully decorated. The staff are attentive and friendly. The coffee was excellent. The menu had a good variety of options. I didn't try the food but I look forward to doing so in the future.
The food is amazing...when they bring it out...which takes forever.
Enjoyed it all

Great breakfast spot with a lot of character and a full bar. It's in a beautiful old room, love the praline bacon. The chicken and waffles and the Sweet Baby Breesus: biscuit sliders with bacon and a boudin ball with some cane syrup. Incredibly delicious and decadent.  I'll definitely be coming back to French Press for breakfast or lunch on my next visit to Lafayette.
The best cajun resteraunt. Get the Cajun Benedict!

Now mind you...the place was not busy. Again we wait. Finally drinks! My husband puts his sweet in low in his tea with lemon and discovers the tea is not tea but coffee?!?!?!? So by this time i start to see my husbands face turn red. I told him to simmer down and to tell the waiter. He tells the waiter...hey dude...smell my tea. The waiter smells and says...dude thats sooo coffee! How did i do that?! Sorry man my bad?!?! I was very excited to eat at the French press but what was meant to be a cool brunch turned into a complete disaster. Any business who has a major known problem (like outrageous wait times) will seek to rectify its problem for the sake of its patronage. There’s likely a problem with the food preparation or the kitchen layout or the ordering system; something. But the French press doesn’t seek such a solution. The staff know there’s a problem, the customers feel the effects of that problem and the owners indirectly feel it because of the lack of turnover in the tables and the revenue that goes with it because customers literally spend half their day getting lunch. The sad part is, it is impossible to not feel a sense of complete disregard for you, the client. An arrogance that’s so thick in the air you can almost taste it.

Our waiter PJ was outstanding, and gave us some tips for other local favs as well

Arrived at restaurant at 10:30 am. Waited 30 minutes for our seats as we were told by hostest. Then waited additional 15 minutes because there was not proper seating to accommodate a high chair (we have a toddler).  We ordered our food as soon as we were seated and it arrived at 11:45 am.  The place is really popular and this creates a long wait for everything. The food is delicious and the staff is very helpful and accommodating. It's not really toddler friendly. If you want a place to sit and chat before having great food then this is a hit. If you want to eat within an hour or have small kids then I'd recommend trying another restaurant.

I can't speak for the food because we didn't get a chance to try it.  This place came highly recommended, and we frequent Lafayette for casual getaways; as a result, we always try to find new food experiences to try and were super excited to try their unique twist on favorite southern dishes.  We paid for an hour of parking at the meter knowing in advance we would have to wait.  We came at a busy time, though there were 2 tables available.  One very close to the front.  When one of the staff (probably the bartender) came to greet us she asked how many and said she would be right with us.  My husband very kindly asked if we could sit at the table that was open near the door.  She turned around and gave him a death stare and said in a very nasty tone "I will be RIGHT WITH YOU!" And stormed off to the bar area where she continued to throw glances back at us.  My husband, being a server himself and generally understanding of busy restaurant situations, was very hurt by this blow up.  For a moment, we decided it would be worth trying to wait, but the longer we waited, even after another server came to greet us and said it would be a minute, eventually leaving became the better option.  Again, we had no issue waiting and fully expected to do so, but the rude outburst to a genuinely polite comment was absolutely uncalled for in our opinion.  We understand when people have bad days, we are human too, but there is no reason to take it out on anyone else--potential customer or otherwise.  We checked the other reviews prior to posting to see if this was an isolated incident which does not seem to be the case and it is very unfortunate.  We have no intention to return considering company culture.
